<!--
    ForgotPassword.fxml defines the JavaFX layout for the "Forgot Password" screen 
    in the GameGrinding application.

    Purpose:
    Provides a secure interface for users to reset their passwords by:
    - Entering their registered email address.
    - Answering three predefined security questions.
    - Creating and confirming a new password.

    Key Components:
    - Email input field with label and placeholder.
    - Three security question labels with corresponding text fields for user answers.
    - New password and confirm password fields for secure credential reset.
    - Submit button (handleResetPassword) to validate inputs and apply password changes.
    - Back button (handleBackButton) to return to the previous screen.
    - Error label for displaying validation or processing messages.

    Visual Design:
    - Dark-themed background with branded images and styled rectangles for section grouping.
    - Buttons and input fields styled with drop shadows and inner shadows for visual depth.
    - Prominent header images and instructional text to guide the reset process.

    Controller:
    Managed by controllers.ForgotPasswordController, which handles field validation,
    password update logic, navigation events, and displaying feedback to the user.
-->

